Alembic migrations for SkillBridge.

Layout
======

- env.py            — runtime entry point; pulls DATABASE_URL from
                       CONFIG_MAP[APP_ENV].DATABASE_URL at runtime.
- script.py.mako    — template for generated migration files.
- versions/         — one file per migration, applied in order.

Common commands
===============

Apply all pending migrations against the current APP_ENV:

    APP_ENV=dev alembic upgrade head

Generate a new migration after editing app/db/models.py (hand-review
the output before committing):

    APP_ENV=dev alembic revision --autogenerate -m "short description"

Roll back one migration:

    APP_ENV=dev alembic downgrade -1

See .kiro/specs/phase-2-persistence/design.md §Alembic Setup and
decisions/ADR-008-alembic-workflow.md for the full workflow.
